Map Visualization¶

Here we are going to display the some Swedish demographic variables and public investments from 2011 to 2020 based on the municipal levels.

All the data comes from Statistics Sweden (SCB). The analysis is used for my master thesis named "The Impact of Swedish Public Finance Factors on the Local Real Estate Market — Based on the GMM PVAR Approach" at KTH.

The red lines are the out-migration rate in Sweden from 2011 to 2020, while the blue lines are the in-migration rate, we can see that their trends are similar, but overall more people move in.

Public investments in Sweden can be seen as the attractive factors for consumers to buy a house. So we listed six main types of government costs here to do some basic data visualization.

Generally speaking, the Swedish government spend most on the educational activities, least on the political activities. The line chart shows that the public investments are quite stable and generally increasing every year.
